Sep 2024 • Family
We walked down to ride this carousel, after we visited the 9/11 museum and memorial. I'm so glad we made the short walk, because this was such a beautiful experience! It's like you are floating with these magical sea creatures. The lights weren't as bright as the website shows, but we were there in the middle of the day. Very peaceful and wonderful thing to do if you are visiting NYC.

DrKatieRN
Bayside, NY1,836 contributions
Beautiful, fun, and unique carousel in battery Park a must visit when in lower Manhattan
Sep 2023 • Family
This is a beautiful and unusual carousel at battery Park. Just a short walk from West Street and from the ferry to the Statue of Liberty. It is very unique. Instead of the usual horses in the carousel, there are sea creatures that light up. Not only do the creatures go up and down. They also go in small circles within the large circular carousel. It is very interesting. We had three generations on the carousel and everyone loved it. The music is coordinated with the theme. It was a genuinely lovely and fun experience for everyone. Additionally, the staff was superb. Josh was fantastic. He helped us find places to sit and even helped a member of our family to step in to the fish. They could not have been nicer. You can even buy a package of 10 rides for a small discount. If you’re in battery Park, I highly recommend listening this lovely carousel. I have traveled the world, and I think this is amongst the nicest carousels, and certainly the most unique, I have ever been in.
Written August 31, 2023
